text: Aline Seitz (born 17 February 1997) is a Swiss racing cyclist. Active on track, road and mountain bike, she is the Swiss champion of the Madison in 2017 and the Omnium in 2018. She rode in the women's scratch event at the 2018 UCI Track Cycling World Championships.Start list ==References== Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:Swiss female cyclists Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Cyclists at the 2019 European Games Category:European Games competitors for Switzerland
